"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-03-paris-2024-olympics-im-not-happy-thierry-henry-fumes-after-france-beat-argentina\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  France U-23 coach, Thierry Henry, was not happy despite their 1-0 win over Argentina in their Olympics football match on Friday night.  There was high tension after the game as both sets of players clashed.  Jean-Philippe Mateta's bullet header in the sixth minute proved to be the winning goal.  Henry's men have now qualified for the semi-finals where they will face Egypt.  There was tension ahead of the game after members of Argentina's triumphant Copa America squad were filmed singing a racist and transphobic chant aimed toward the French.  Chelsea midfielder, Enzo Fernandez, livestreamed the video on Instagram, with his club team-mate and France defender Wesley Fofana describing it as \\\"uninhibited racism\\\".  French supporters booed and jeered Argentina's squad at the Nouveau Stade de Bordeaux before and during the match.  And it all culminated in the ugly clash at full time, resulting in Enzo Millot being shown a red card.  Speaking afterwards, Henry said: \\\"I do not agree with what happened at the end of the match. My player [Millot] got a red card and I do not accept it, it should not happen.  \\\"I could not control what happened. I went to greet the coach and when I turned around, what happened happened.  \\\"We won, but I did not like what happened at the end with my player.\\\"  Olympics 2024: Sports Minister updates on Favour Ofili's 100m race exclusion, raises posers  Transfer: Maresca breaks silence after banning Chelsea player from dressing room  UCL: 'That's not victory' - Thierry Henry on what Bar\\u00e7a did to Newcastle  EPL: A lot of people do not want Arsenal to win title - Thierry Henry  EPL: Thierry Henry gives Man Utd captain, Bruno Fernandes new nickname  'Can we be fair' - Thierry Henry defends Mbappe  UCL: Thierry Henry names two clubs to win trophy this season  UCL: 'Victor how body dey' - Thierry Henry speaks pidgin English to Osimhen  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"